sections.body:
Create the AWS EventBridge Trigger with error handling enabled via a
`POST` request to the
[Create a Trigger](atlas/app-services/admin/api/v3)
endpoint.

```bash
curl -X POST \
   https://services.cloud.mongodb.com/api/admin/v3.0/groups/{groupId}/apps/{appId}/triggers \
   -H 'Authorization: Bearer <access_token>' \
   -d '{
         "name": "string",
         "type": "DATABASE",
         "config": {
            "service_id": "string",
            "database": "string",
            "collection": "string",
            "operation_types": {
               "string"
            },
            "match": ,
            "full_document": false,
            "full_document_before_change": false,
            "unordered": true
         },
         "event_processors": {
            "AWS_EVENTBRIDGE": {
               "account_id": "string",
               "region": "string",
               "extended_json_enabled": false
            },
         },
         "error_handler": {
            "enabled": true,
            "function_id": "string"
         }
      }'
```

